## Output formats
Reports and plans default to **Markdown** (terminal/PR/repo-friendly). When I ask for HTML
(say "as HTML", or use `/report-html`), produce one **self-contained** `.html` file — inline
`<style>` + vanilla `<script>`, no external deps, works offline — saved under `docs/reports/`.
Output raw HTML only (no Markdown, no prose outside the file).

**Style — Catppuccin Mocha (dark):** bg `#1e1e2e`, surface `#313244`, text `#cdd6f4`, muted
`#a6adc8`, accent `#cba6f7`, links `#89b4fa`, success `#a6e3a1`, warning `#f9e2af`. System
font stack ~16px, generous line-height, rounded corners, subtle borders.

**Use semantic HTML only where it aids comprehension** (don't force it): sticky table of
contents / anchor links for multi-section docs; styled zebra tables with a sticky header for
comparisons; `<progress>` or styled meters for any metric, score, or completion; inline SVG
for flows, architecture, or relationships; collapsible `<details>`, tabs, and copy-to-clipboard
on code blocks; styled code blocks plus callout/admonition boxes for notes and warnings.

## Codebase knowledge graph (graphify)
When a graph exists (`graphify-out/graph.json`):
- "how does X work / what calls Y / trace this flow" → `graphify query "<question>"`
- relationship between two things → `graphify path "<A>" "<B>"`
- focus on one concept → `graphify explain "<concept>"`
- Prefer these over broad grep/file dumps. After changing code, run `graphify update .`.

## Optional tooling (use when configured)
- **ast-grep** (if installed) for exact structural search and safe codemods:
  `ast-grep -p '<pattern>' -l <lang>` (rewrite with `-r '<replacement>'`). Prefer it
  over regex for structure-aware matches/refactors; use graphify to orient first.
- **MCP servers** (if configured in `.mcp.json` / `.codex/config.toml` / `.vscode/mcp.json`):
  Context7 for up-to-date library docs, Grep for real-world usage across public repos,
  private-journal for cross-session memory.

